==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: packer
<hw>pack"er</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧k"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A person whose business is to pack things; especially, one who
packs food for preservation or for the market; <as>as, a pork
<ex>packer</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A ring of packing or a special device to render
gas-tight and water-tight the space between the tubing and bore of an
oil well.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Packera</ent>⟦br⟧
